WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:08.175 --> 00:00:12.012
The morning God Flame has finally risen
to give us a bit of warmth. Princess.

2
00:00:13.555 --> 00:00:14.890
[door opens]

3
00:00:16.225 --> 00:00:18.060
[bells jingling]

4
00:00:19.311 --> 00:00:21.063
[Harmony] Good morning. Your Majesty.

5
00:00:22.606 --> 00:00:24.608
[Queen Kane]
It is a beautiful day. Maghra.

6
00:00:24.691 --> 00:00:26.985
The entire city will rejoice with you.

7
00:00:27.528 --> 00:00:31.907
It is a shame Father couldn't be here
with us to celebrate your wedding day.

8
00:00:36.119 --> 00:00:37.120
[sighs]

9
00:00:38.288 --> 00:00:40.916
Lilac. lavender and honey.

10
00:00:41.959 --> 00:00:44.795
-[Maghra sighs]
-You'll make the most appealing bride.

11
00:00:45.838 --> 00:00:46.839
Leave that.

12
00:00:47.548 --> 00:00:50.384
Princess. you must be completely
unadorned for the marriage ceremony.

13
00:00:50.467 --> 00:00:53.512
-No. I will not remove this cuff.
-It's the law of the land.

14
00:00:53.595 --> 00:00:55.973
Handmaiden. what is your name?

15
00:00:57.266 --> 00:00:58.809
Harmony. Your Majesty.

16
00:00:58.892 --> 00:01:01.603
Harmony? That is a beautiful name.

17
00:01:03.063 --> 00:01:04.438
Give me your hand. Harmony.

18
00:01:04.522 --> 00:01:06.775
[bells jingling]

19
00:01:10.445 --> 00:01:11.947
Harmony.

20
00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:16.118
are you in the habit of telling princesses
what they may and may not do?

21
00:01:16.201 --> 00:01:19.204
Perhaps you would tell your queen as well?

22
00:01:19.288 --> 00:01:21.206
[gasps] No. Your Majesty. never.

23
00:01:21.290 --> 00:01:22.958
Then hush and leave her.

24
00:01:28.213 --> 00:01:32.509
Hmm. The princess is fully slathered.
You may go. Harmony.

25
00:01:32.593 --> 00:01:33.635
Yes. Your Majesty.

26
00:01:36.513 --> 00:01:37.556
[sighs]

27
00:01:42.895 --> 00:01:44.021
[door closes]

28
00:01:44.104 --> 00:01:47.691
The Pennsan people.
and that means all of them.

29
00:01:47.774 --> 00:01:52.821
even insignificant servants.
must believe this is a true union.

30
00:01:52.905 --> 00:01:55.240
Don't worry. I will play my part.

31
00:01:55.324 --> 00:01:57.034
You're not in this alone.

32
00:01:57.117 --> 00:02:00.746
Yes. I am.
You are not the one being unfaithful.

33
00:02:02.539 --> 00:02:03.582
[sighs]

34
00:02:04.791 --> 00:02:07.461
This marriage will serve us all.

35
00:02:08.044 --> 00:02:10.964
When your children are found
and brought here to you.

36
00:02:11.048 --> 00:02:13.592
it'll be this arrangement
that'll keep them safe.

37
00:02:14.468 --> 00:02:17.846
[tuning fork echoes]

38
00:02:19.056 --> 00:02:22.226
Some people would be insulted
by their sister tuning them out.

39
00:02:22.309 --> 00:02:24.728
Sibeth. you can never be silenced.

40
00:02:24.811 --> 00:02:26.355
God knows I've tried.

41
00:02:34.947 --> 00:02:35.948
Here.

42
00:02:38.492 --> 00:02:42.871
Remember when you were little.
and I'd wash your hair?

43
00:03:05.394 --> 00:03:06.645
Don't stop.

44
00:03:11.066 --> 00:03:12.067
Please.

45
00:05:07.850 --> 00:05:10.936
Can you please just-- just stay back?

46
00:05:11.019 --> 00:05:13.647
I promise you. no one is going
to kill me on this path.

47
00:05:13.730 --> 00:05:15.858
Yeah. well. not with me here. they're not.

48
00:05:15.941 --> 00:05:19.027
Haniwa. Haniwa. wait for me.

49
00:05:19.111 --> 00:05:21.697
[grunts. sighs]

50
00:05:21.780 --> 00:05:27.744
Listen. there's no harm in having
a-- a dedicated warrior by your side.

51
00:05:27.828 --> 00:05:30.038
I know I'm grateful
for you and your arrows.

52
00:05:32.833 --> 00:05:34.293
I can hear you thinking.

53
00:05:35.252 --> 00:05:36.336
[scoffs]

54
00:05:38.463 --> 00:05:41.216
Yesterday. I was mourning my mother.

55
00:05:42.134 --> 00:05:44.178
Today. she is a living princess.

56
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:48.515
and I am thinking back
on every moment of my childhood.

57
00:05:49.308 --> 00:05:52.102
wondering what was true and what still is.

58
00:05:54.438 --> 00:05:56.190
We will know soon. my love.

59
00:05:57.232 --> 00:05:58.609
Not soon enough.

60
00:06:00.569 --> 00:06:01.737
[Paris groans]

61
00:06:02.529 --> 00:06:03.614
[sighs. exclaims]

62
00:06:04.656 --> 00:06:07.576
You know. uh. I'm not a threat to you.

63
00:06:10.204 --> 00:06:12.706
You mistake my contempt for fear.

64
00:06:15.667 --> 00:06:20.464
Tell me. Witchfinder General.
how many lives have you taken?

65
00:06:21.715 --> 00:06:24.968
Enough to damn my soul many times over.

66
00:06:26.887 --> 00:06:30.182
And yet. you will kill the queen
whom you have served.

67
00:06:31.725 --> 00:06:34.019
There is not enough damnation for you.

68
00:06:35.145 --> 00:06:38.190
No. I suspect not.

69
00:06:39.691 --> 00:06:41.985
[panting]

70
00:06:45.197 --> 00:06:46.365
Mmm.

71
00:06:46.448 --> 00:06:49.284
-Are you all right?
-Yeah. I'm fine.

72
00:06:50.452 --> 00:06:54.122
-We should've stayed another night.
-Nah. it's nothing.

73
00:06:55.207 --> 00:06:58.252
If your head fell off. you would
pick it up and carry it to Pennsa.

74
00:06:59.211 --> 00:07:01.338
No. I would make you carry it.

75
00:07:01.421 --> 00:07:03.882
-[chuckles]
-[chuckles] Ouch.

76
00:07:03.966 --> 00:07:06.218
[banging]

77
00:07:06.301 --> 00:07:08.053
These brave soldiers died

78
00:07:08.136 --> 00:07:12.724
trying to stop the murderer. Baba Voss.
from escaping Trivantes.

79
00:07:13.392 --> 00:07:16.353
They died heroes.
and they will be avenged.

80
00:07:16.436 --> 00:07:17.771
[sobbing]

81
00:07:17.855 --> 00:07:20.482
A valiant soldier
of the republic remembered forever.

82
00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:25.404
A sacred son of Trivantes.
now one with us.

83
00:07:26.196 --> 00:07:27.948
[woman crying]

84
00:07:33.829 --> 00:07:36.331
[woman] Rendayo. My son.

85
00:07:42.880 --> 00:07:44.006
Madame Orrie.

86
00:07:45.757 --> 00:07:48.135
Rendayo was a patriot and a hero.

87
00:07:48.218 --> 00:07:49.511
[sniffling]

88
00:07:49.595 --> 00:07:53.473
I immensely admired him
as if he were my own son.

89
00:07:55.976 --> 00:08:00.230
Those responsible for his death
will suffer. You have my word.

90
00:08:01.231 --> 00:08:04.735
[woman cries]

91
00:08:12.117 --> 00:08:13.118
[sniffles]

92
00:08:16.038 --> 00:08:21.460
[crying]

93
00:08:33.639 --> 00:08:35.182
You have news for me?

94
00:08:35.265 --> 00:08:39.061
Yes. General Voss.
A Witchfinder looking for asylum.

95
00:08:39.144 --> 00:08:40.312
A Witchfinder.

96
00:08:40.395 --> 00:08:42.231
If true. this will be the first time

97
00:08:42.313 --> 00:08:44.358
one of Tamacti Jun's soldiers
has broken ranks.

98
00:08:46.735 --> 00:08:47.945
What is he trading?

99
00:08:48.028 --> 00:08:50.864
He insists he will speak only to you.

100
00:08:50.948 --> 00:08:51.949
Ah.

101
00:08:52.616 --> 00:08:54.618
And he will likely regret that.

102
00:08:55.118 --> 00:08:56.119
Bring him to me.

103
00:08:57.287 --> 00:09:00.290
-[guard] Come on.
-[grunting. groaning]

104
00:09:06.964 --> 00:09:12.386
I am Commander General Edo Voss.
and I understand you wish to speak to me.

105
00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:13.470
Yes. sir.

106
00:09:13.554 --> 00:09:16.390
You are the first
of the queen's Witchfinders that I've met

107
00:09:16.473 --> 00:09:20.310
that wasn't already impaled
on the end of my sword.

108
00:09:20.936 --> 00:09:22.855
I have information you will want. sir.

109
00:09:24.398 --> 00:09:29.570
And why would I trust a soldier
who betrays his own kingdom?

110
00:09:29.653 --> 00:09:32.781
My kingdom is no longer
the kingdom I swore to defend.

111
00:09:33.282 --> 00:09:34.408
And how's that?

112
00:09:34.992 --> 00:09:36.827
I am sworn to protect the Payan kingdom

113
00:09:36.910 --> 00:09:38.996
from the evils of witchcraft
and therefore--

114
00:09:39.079 --> 00:09:42.374
I am familiar with Witchfinders. boy.

115
00:09:42.457 --> 00:09:45.502
Including those who might have sight
or seek to facilitate its return.

116
00:09:46.378 --> 00:09:49.256
[Edo Voss] And now.
your queen decrees that the sighted

117
00:09:49.339 --> 00:09:51.175
are. in fact. not witches.

118
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.803
[stammers] Yes. sir.

119
00:09:54.887 --> 00:10:00.142
In fact. she also claims to be
carrying a sighted child in her own womb.

120
00:10:01.268 --> 00:10:02.269
Yes. sir.

121
00:10:02.352 --> 00:10:08.650
Boy. did you really desert your own army
and face certain death

122
00:10:08.734 --> 00:10:13.280
to come here and tell me something
my spies reported days ago?

123
00:10:15.616 --> 00:10:19.036
-Hobble him and sell him to the Slavers.
-[Dax] No. no.

124
00:10:19.119 --> 00:10:20.454
-[guard] Come on.
-Sir.

125
00:10:21.246 --> 00:10:23.916
-Commander Voss. there are others.
-[Edo Voss] Stop!

126
00:10:35.135 --> 00:10:36.136
Others?

127
00:10:37.179 --> 00:10:40.974
Hers won't be the first sighted child
within the Payan royal family.

128
00:10:41.517 --> 00:10:43.519
There are two. already grown.

129
00:10:47.648 --> 00:10:49.608
And these children already grown…

130
00:10:51.610 --> 00:10:55.739
is one of them a girl called Haniwa?

131
00:10:57.282 --> 00:10:58.283
[Dax] Yes.

132
00:11:00.744 --> 00:11:01.745
[Edo Voss] Mmm.

133
00:11:32.025 --> 00:11:33.402
So. this is Pennsa?

134
00:11:36.154 --> 00:11:37.155
Yes.

135
00:11:46.540 --> 00:11:47.875
Is it always this quiet?

136
00:11:49.877 --> 00:11:53.046
[sighs] No. Never.

137
00:11:56.550 --> 00:11:57.634
Something's wrong.

138
00:12:07.686 --> 00:12:09.146
There's soldiers ahead.

139
00:12:12.733 --> 00:12:14.484
Stay here and say nothing.

140
00:12:15.485 --> 00:12:18.447
-Uh. should we be worried?
-Not we. you.

141
00:12:39.635 --> 00:12:41.803
-[horse nickers]
-[Toad sighs]

142
00:12:43.055 --> 00:12:45.807
-This is gonna be tricky.
-Why? Isn't my mother here?

143
00:12:45.891 --> 00:12:48.310
-She's here.
-So. what's the problem?

144
00:12:49.311 --> 00:12:51.230
The thing of it is… [sighs]

145
00:12:51.313 --> 00:12:53.232
…she's apparently getting married today.

146
00:13:10.165 --> 00:13:11.333
Baba. my love…

147
00:13:13.252 --> 00:13:14.294
forgive me.

148
00:13:16.338 --> 00:13:17.339
[Kofun] Mom?

149
00:13:19.758 --> 00:13:20.592
Mom!

150
00:13:21.426 --> 00:13:22.427
Kofun?

151
00:13:23.387 --> 00:13:27.140
-Mom. Mom! Mom! [chuckles]
-[gasps]

152
00:13:28.642 --> 00:13:32.729
Whew. [gasps] You're alive.

153
00:13:32.813 --> 00:13:34.064
My baby.

154
00:13:35.774 --> 00:13:40.404
Oh. I've searched for you
every day since we were separated.

155
00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:42.865
I never stopped.

156
00:13:42.948 --> 00:13:47.703
Mmm. Mom they said
that you're getting married today.

157
00:13:47.786 --> 00:13:49.705
That can't be true. can it? [inhales]

158
00:13:50.414 --> 00:13:51.874
I will explain everything.

159
00:13:53.917 --> 00:13:56.211
Where's your father? And Haniwa?

160
00:13:57.546 --> 00:13:59.715
He went into Trivantes to get her back.

161
00:13:59.798 --> 00:14:00.799
Trivantes?

162
00:14:00.883 --> 00:14:02.968
-[knocking]
-[Harmony] Princess Maghra. it's time.

163
00:14:03.051 --> 00:14:06.597
Wait. Why-- Why Trivantes?

164
00:14:06.680 --> 00:14:09.266
-What happened with Jerlamarel?
-How can you be getting married today?

165
00:14:09.349 --> 00:14:11.351
[Harmony] Lord Harlan is waiting.
and the queen is growing impatient.

166
00:14:11.435 --> 00:14:13.187
-I'm coming.
-Who is Lord Harlan?

167
00:14:13.812 --> 00:14:15.731
I will explain everything later.
I have to go. Kofun.

168
00:14:15.814 --> 00:14:19.359
-I just need you to trust me.
-Mama? [whispers] Mama. you can't do this.

169
00:14:19.443 --> 00:14:21.945
I-- I can't stop this.

170
00:14:22.571 --> 00:14:23.572
Your father would understand.

171
00:14:23.655 --> 00:14:26.992
No. I don't think he would understand why
his dead wife is marrying someone else.

172
00:14:27.075 --> 00:14:28.410
-Kofun--
-Stop saying my name

173
00:14:28.493 --> 00:14:29.995
and do something to fix this!

174
00:14:30.078 --> 00:14:33.373
I-- I don't know what is happening.
Mama. but you can't go through with it.

175
00:14:33.457 --> 00:14:34.625
Be quiet!

176
00:14:35.459 --> 00:14:39.463
I am still the mother you knew.
and you are still my son.

177
00:14:40.422 --> 00:14:42.216
But things have changed.

178
00:14:43.759 --> 00:14:46.803
Now. I'm doing this for you
and for all of us.

179
00:14:48.013 --> 00:14:51.141
So you stay here.
You stay here in my room.

180
00:14:51.808 --> 00:14:53.268
and you speak to no one.

181
00:14:54.520 --> 00:14:58.106
and then we will talk
when all of this is over. I promise.

182
00:15:00.359 --> 00:15:03.278
-I promise.
-[grunts] D-Don't do this.

183
00:15:05.155 --> 00:15:06.657
-Don't do this.
-I have to.

184
00:15:17.209 --> 00:15:20.295
I have so many questions.

185
00:15:21.255 --> 00:15:24.967
[Baba Voss retches. sniffs. groans]

186
00:15:25.884 --> 00:15:28.679
[coughing]

187
00:15:29.263 --> 00:15:30.889
-[coughs]
-All right. that's enough.

188
00:15:30.973 --> 00:15:33.392
-Ah. I just need a moment. [sighs]
-Paris?

189
00:15:33.475 --> 00:15:35.143
-[Baba Voss grunts]
-[panting]

190
00:15:35.227 --> 00:15:38.021
[Baba Voss grunts. sighs]

191
00:15:38.814 --> 00:15:40.691
-[grunts] Woman.
-Oh!

192
00:15:40.774 --> 00:15:43.193
I feel the fever through your clothing.

193
00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:46.864
-It's not gonna kill me.
-You need a healer.

194
00:15:47.364 --> 00:15:48.782
We'll find one in Pennsa.

195
00:15:48.866 --> 00:15:51.493
Baba.
You'll be dead by the time we get there.

196
00:15:53.203 --> 00:15:56.123
We are in the Lakelands now.
not far from the Valier.

197
00:15:56.206 --> 00:15:58.542
They will offer us shelter and a healer.

198
00:15:59.418 --> 00:16:00.419
Papa?

199
00:16:01.712 --> 00:16:04.506
-[sighs]
-Please.

200
00:16:06.508 --> 00:16:07.801
Okay. my love.

201
00:16:08.677 --> 00:16:11.680
[Tamacti Jun] I cannot accompany you
to Valier territory.

202
00:16:12.222 --> 00:16:14.099
Well. that is where we are going.

203
00:16:14.183 --> 00:16:17.144
Understand. the hidden tribes
were not hidden to me.

204
00:16:18.020 --> 00:16:20.689
The Valier suffered greatly at my hands.

205
00:16:29.364 --> 00:16:33.702
You stay quiet and camp nearby.
We'll find you on the way out.

206
00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:36.705
[sighs. sniffles]

207
00:16:38.123 --> 00:16:39.208
Or not.

208
00:16:41.168 --> 00:16:42.169
[spits]

209
00:16:42.669 --> 00:16:43.837
[Baba Voss groans]

210
00:17:06.983 --> 00:17:12.906
[Queen Kane. crowd vocalizing]

211
00:17:27.506 --> 00:17:30.884
Our God. beyond your flame above…

212
00:17:32.970 --> 00:17:35.597
let your will be done on this special day

213
00:17:35.681 --> 00:17:38.058
in this holiest of unions.

214
00:17:40.060 --> 00:17:43.522
Give guidance. clear paths.

215
00:17:43.605 --> 00:17:49.903
condemn those who trespass against us
to writhe within your fire and smoke.

216
00:17:51.154 --> 00:17:57.327
For Thine is the darkness.
the power and the glory.

217
00:17:58.954 --> 00:18:00.873
Forever and ever.

218
00:18:23.729 --> 00:18:28.025
Princess Maghra and Lord Harlan…

219
00:18:32.654 --> 00:18:35.824
you enter this union
adorned in scented splendor.

220
00:18:43.207 --> 00:18:44.791
[clicks tongue]

221
00:18:48.921 --> 00:18:50.339
[clicks tongue]

222
00:18:55.969 --> 00:18:58.805
You've pledged
your commitment to each other

223
00:18:58.889 --> 00:19:02.017
with the joining of bodies and souls
before God.

224
00:19:03.727 --> 00:19:10.692
So. by the divine ordination
bestowed upon me. you may seal your union.

225
00:19:18.325 --> 00:19:22.955
[cheering]

226
00:19:40.180 --> 00:19:42.015
[bells jingling]

227
00:20:44.244 --> 00:20:45.829
-[woman murmurs]
-Thank you. you too.

228
00:20:47.039 --> 00:20:48.165
-[man shouts]
-[gasps]

229
00:20:49.499 --> 00:20:50.834
[sighs]

230
00:20:51.418 --> 00:20:53.378
Princess Maghra.

231
00:20:55.130 --> 00:20:59.843
-Any wife of Harlan's is a sister of mine.
-Maghra. you remember my brother.

232
00:21:00.552 --> 00:21:04.932
-[Harlan] Thank you.
-Kerrigan. I changed your diapers.

233
00:21:05.516 --> 00:21:08.352
Well. Lucky for all of us.
I have people for that now.

234
00:21:08.435 --> 00:21:10.896
[chuckles. sniffs. grunts]

235
00:21:10.979 --> 00:21:12.648
[chuckles]

236
00:21:12.731 --> 00:21:14.358
-Thank you.
-[Maghra chuckles] Oh.

237
00:21:15.567 --> 00:21:17.736
-[Harlan] Thank you so much.
-Oh.

238
00:21:17.819 --> 00:21:19.821
-I'm sorry. Sorry.
-[Kerrigan] Mmm.

239
00:21:20.864 --> 00:21:23.033
All right. Go. go. Get off. Go.

240
00:21:36.839 --> 00:21:39.216
-[Charlotte] Are we close?
-[Paris] Yes.

241
00:21:39.299 --> 00:21:41.510
Because I don't think
the big one can make it much further.

242
00:21:41.593 --> 00:21:43.220
and I don't think
we'll be able to carry him.

243
00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:44.471
[shushes]

244
00:21:46.640 --> 00:21:48.392
-Who's there?
-[metal scraping]

245
00:21:48.475 --> 00:21:49.518
Make yourself known.

246
00:21:49.601 --> 00:21:52.813
[man] Who enters Valier territory
without announcing themselves?

247
00:21:53.438 --> 00:21:57.651
Brother! We bring no threat. I am Paris.

248
00:21:57.734 --> 00:21:59.695
We are the last of the Alkenny.

249
00:21:59.778 --> 00:22:03.073
No. I am last of the Alkenny.

250
00:22:04.408 --> 00:22:06.785
-Chet-chet.
-Chet-chet-chet.

251
00:22:06.869 --> 00:22:08.620
Bow! [chuckling. exclaiming]

252
00:22:09.121 --> 00:22:10.205
Lion.

253
00:22:10.289 --> 00:22:15.335
-[Paris] Ah. Bow Lion. [chuckles]
-[chuckles]

254
00:22:15.419 --> 00:22:16.712
[sniffs] Oh. Paris.

255
00:22:44.406 --> 00:22:45.407
[Queen Kane] Kofun?

256
00:22:46.992 --> 00:22:48.368
-Is it you?
-[sword clatters]

257
00:22:50.370 --> 00:22:51.538
It's okay. You're safe.

258
00:22:52.664 --> 00:22:53.707
I'm your Aunt Sibeth.

259
00:22:57.002 --> 00:23:00.422
I was overjoyed
when I heard you were finally here.

260
00:23:00.506 --> 00:23:03.217
We've been waiting
such a long time for you.

261
00:23:04.384 --> 00:23:07.137
[bells jingling]

262
00:23:12.559 --> 00:23:13.769
Will you embrace me?

263
00:23:24.738 --> 00:23:27.741
[gasping]

264
00:23:29.284 --> 00:23:30.369
[gasps]

265
00:23:36.667 --> 00:23:38.418
You're taller than your parents.

266
00:23:41.421 --> 00:23:44.925
Would you like something?
Anything to drink? I'll send for it.

267
00:23:45.008 --> 00:23:47.553
No. Thank you.

268
00:23:49.096 --> 00:23:52.307
How tragic we're only meeting now
for the first time.

269
00:23:54.476 --> 00:23:56.311
You hunted us my whole life.

270
00:24:00.399 --> 00:24:02.776
If only Maghra
had announced herself long ago.

271
00:24:02.860 --> 00:24:06.029
I would've protected her. protected you.

272
00:24:07.114 --> 00:24:08.323
She knew that.

273
00:24:09.533 --> 00:24:12.578
We were hunting Jerlamarel
and his children.

274
00:24:12.661 --> 00:24:14.329
I didn't know they were Maghra's.

275
00:24:15.038 --> 00:24:18.792
I'd been led to believe
Jerlamarel had killed my sister.

276
00:24:18.876 --> 00:24:20.169
I believed him to be the devil.

277
00:24:20.252 --> 00:24:23.422
You know that's not true.
Why'd my mother stay hidden?

278
00:24:24.923 --> 00:24:26.466
Whatever mistakes she made.

279
00:24:27.593 --> 00:24:31.013
I'm sure she made them
to keep you and your sister safe.

280
00:24:31.638 --> 00:24:33.307
which is what I'm trying to do right now.

281
00:24:33.390 --> 00:24:35.851
Well. even with your decree.

282
00:24:35.934 --> 00:24:38.437
people in Paya still believe
a witch is to be burned.

283
00:24:38.520 --> 00:24:40.647
I've been known to change a few minds.

284
00:24:41.648 --> 00:24:43.525
It might take a bit of time.

285
00:24:43.609 --> 00:24:48.947
but the Payans will learn. as I have.

286
00:24:50.741 --> 00:24:54.119
to embrace those with sight as blessed.

287
00:24:59.625 --> 00:25:01.210
How difficult for you.

288
00:25:02.711 --> 00:25:06.423
journeying to this place.
arriving on your mother's wedding day.

289
00:25:07.049 --> 00:25:08.675
The world must seem upside down.

290
00:25:10.844 --> 00:25:12.387
But know this.

291
00:25:13.180 --> 00:25:17.351
no one shall stand against you.
not while you're in my kingdom.

292
00:25:18.602 --> 00:25:20.145
Do you believe me?

293
00:25:24.274 --> 00:25:25.275
I don't know.

294
00:25:26.818 --> 00:25:27.861
I want to.

295
00:25:29.821 --> 00:25:30.948
Fair enough.

296
00:25:32.115 --> 00:25:35.577
Many good things start with… desire.

297
00:25:36.411 --> 00:25:38.539
[inhales]

298
00:25:40.207 --> 00:25:42.376
-[chuckles]
-[breathes heavily]

299
00:25:43.961 --> 00:25:47.172
I've arranged a room for you.
We'll talk again soon?

300
00:26:05.274 --> 00:26:07.943
[Edo Voss] Queen Kane's war council
is mobilizing her armies.

301
00:26:08.443 --> 00:26:11.738
And we've learned from the Payan defector

302
00:26:11.822 --> 00:26:13.949
that not only has
Princess Maghra returned.

303
00:26:14.575 --> 00:26:17.452
but she comes with two grown children.
Haniwa and Kofun.

304
00:26:18.745 --> 00:26:19.955
Both sighted.

305
00:26:20.038 --> 00:26:23.125
The Payan fanatics
will burn them at the stake.

306
00:26:24.084 --> 00:26:25.878
[Edo Voss]
They will do as their queen commands.

307
00:26:25.961 --> 00:26:28.922
With two sighted children
in the royal family now of age.

308
00:26:29.631 --> 00:26:31.300
they are an even greater threat.

309
00:26:31.383 --> 00:26:33.552
[The Military]
We don't know their intentions.

310
00:26:33.635 --> 00:26:34.720
We know they took the trouble

311
00:26:34.803 --> 00:26:37.222
to break their Witchfinder General
out of captivity.

312
00:26:38.015 --> 00:26:40.475
That is intention enough.
We must strike now.

313
00:26:40.559 --> 00:26:44.438
It would be suicide
for the Payans to attack us.

314
00:26:45.689 --> 00:26:48.984
The queen may be crazy.
but she's not a fool.

315
00:26:49.067 --> 00:26:52.029
Still. these are troubling developments.

316
00:26:53.113 --> 00:26:54.406
I can muster our forces in a matter of d--

317
00:26:54.489 --> 00:26:55.782
No. steady. Edo.

318
00:26:56.700 --> 00:27:00.204
The Ganites
are still raining shit on us out west.

319
00:27:00.287 --> 00:27:03.290
And you yourself stood here
and heard the council's attitude

320
00:27:03.373 --> 00:27:04.917
about an eastern campaign.

321
00:27:05.000 --> 00:27:08.337
-You will never sell it.
-No. You will do that.

322
00:27:08.420 --> 00:27:10.631
[The Military]
You overestimate my influence.

323
00:27:10.714 --> 00:27:13.008
I am but one third of the Triangle.

324
00:27:14.885 --> 00:27:15.886
But still.

325
00:27:16.595 --> 00:27:21.058
I will convince the council to request
a diplomatic summit with the Payans.

326
00:27:21.141 --> 00:27:24.645
-Trivantians do not sue for peace!
-We do what we need to do.

327
00:27:25.437 --> 00:27:28.273
And you will do as ordered.
Do you understand?

328
00:27:31.568 --> 00:27:32.694
Yes. sir.

329
00:27:32.778 --> 00:27:36.740
If for nothing else. it will give us time
to bring a battalion or two east.

330
00:27:36.823 --> 00:27:39.201
if it comes to that.

331
00:27:39.868 --> 00:27:41.161
Understood.

332
00:27:44.581 --> 00:27:48.043
I will let you know
what the council decides.

333
00:28:03.475 --> 00:28:07.646
[Bow Lion] Breathe slow and deep. Baba.
and drink this.

334
00:28:07.729 --> 00:28:11.358
[tapping cup]

335
00:28:11.441 --> 00:28:13.402
-It will give you strength.
-[sighs]

336
00:28:19.908 --> 00:28:22.286
[groans] When did you become a healer?

337
00:28:23.579 --> 00:28:27.416
I'm not yet. but I've been learning
from the healers here.

338
00:28:30.210 --> 00:28:33.547
Those roots should absorb the infections
so that the fever can pass.

339
00:28:34.798 --> 00:28:38.510
You've lost so much. all because of us.

340
00:28:40.554 --> 00:28:41.889
Still. you take us in.

341
00:28:46.351 --> 00:28:47.895
[Bow Lion] We are one tribe. remember?

342
00:28:52.566 --> 00:28:53.817
Yeah. I remember.

343
00:29:23.889 --> 00:29:26.892
[breathing heavily]

344
00:29:38.278 --> 00:29:39.488
[bells jingling]

345
00:29:40.405 --> 00:29:41.406
[Maghra] Kofun?

346
00:29:42.366 --> 00:29:44.201
[Harlan] No. Not Kofun.

347
00:29:46.453 --> 00:29:47.996
[Maghra] What are you doing in here?

348
00:29:48.664 --> 00:29:52.125
Maghra. it's our wedding night.
Where else am I gonna be?

349
00:29:53.544 --> 00:29:55.462
[bells jingling]

350
00:29:55.546 --> 00:29:58.215
This is not a marriage.
This is an alliance.

351
00:29:58.715 --> 00:30:01.885
Right. but-- but it can be both.

352
00:30:06.807 --> 00:30:09.268
Put on your pants. Harlan.
I need your help.

353
00:30:11.103 --> 00:30:12.312
-Now.
-Fine.

354
00:30:14.898 --> 00:30:15.899
[Harlan grunts]

355
00:30:31.331 --> 00:30:33.333
[tapping]

356
00:30:36.879 --> 00:30:39.256
They made me sneak you
some pheasant and ale.

357
00:30:39.965 --> 00:30:42.718
Don't worry. I didn't poison it.
if that's what you're thinking.

358
00:30:44.928 --> 00:30:46.263
I had no such thought.

359
00:30:46.972 --> 00:30:48.807
And I had no such poison.

360
00:30:48.891 --> 00:30:50.058
[plate clatters]

361
00:30:50.142 --> 00:30:51.602
[liquid sloshes]

362
00:30:53.270 --> 00:30:55.564
[Andal] Our Alkenny brothers and sisters.

363
00:30:55.647 --> 00:30:58.400
last time you came to us.
we turned you away.

364
00:30:58.942 --> 00:31:02.654
You healed our Bow Lion.
It is more than we could've hoped for.

365
00:31:02.738 --> 00:31:06.408
It is you who bring us
a message of hope upon your return.

366
00:31:06.867 --> 00:31:09.328
We feared that you would
lead Witchfinders to us.

367
00:31:09.411 --> 00:31:13.749
because when they had come prior. they
said the sighted hid amongst the Alkenny.

368
00:31:14.333 --> 00:31:15.334
-[swords clashing]
-[women screaming]

369
00:31:15.417 --> 00:31:19.338
They slaughtered men. women. children.

370
00:31:20.589 --> 00:31:22.382
Their blades didn't discriminate.

371
00:31:23.425 --> 00:31:26.720
all because the Witchfinders believed
we had knowledge of witches.

372
00:31:26.803 --> 00:31:27.638
[screams echoing]

373
00:31:27.721 --> 00:31:30.766
Those of us who lived
were spared only to spread the fear.

374
00:31:33.268 --> 00:31:37.272
But we will rebuild.
We're already making babies.

375
00:31:38.106 --> 00:31:42.986
We will make ourselves whole to honor
the memory of the many that were lost.

376
00:31:43.070 --> 00:31:45.948
[screams echoing]

377
00:31:46.031 --> 00:31:47.115
Stop!

378
00:31:49.785 --> 00:31:54.164
[Andal] And now word comes that the queen
will no longer send her Witchfinders.

379
00:31:54.248 --> 00:31:56.375
as she no longer searches for witches.

380
00:31:58.669 --> 00:32:00.712
The queen may yet change her mind.

381
00:32:00.796 --> 00:32:06.885
but tonight. we celebrate your escape
from Trivantes and savor our freedom…

382
00:32:06.969 --> 00:32:08.595
[signaling] Tamacti Jun is here.

383
00:32:08.679 --> 00:32:11.932
…however short-lived.
from the queen and her Witchfinders.

384
00:32:12.015 --> 00:32:13.308
[tapping]

385
00:32:13.392 --> 00:32:15.727
[Andal] These are uncertain times.

386
00:32:15.811 --> 00:32:17.813
but we face them with hope

387
00:32:17.896 --> 00:32:20.983
for a future more peaceful than our past.

388
00:32:22.943 --> 00:32:24.403
[grunts]

389
00:32:25.571 --> 00:32:27.447
-Have you lost your mind?
-[grunts]

390
00:32:28.448 --> 00:32:32.160
The Valier deserve retribution.
I owe 'em that much.

391
00:32:32.244 --> 00:32:33.829
[Baba Voss] No. you owe me. Witchfinder.

392
00:32:33.912 --> 00:32:37.541
You think I don't wanna rip your throat
out every time I hear your voice?

393
00:32:39.418 --> 00:32:41.128
You slaughtered my people too.

394
00:32:42.880 --> 00:32:44.464
But you do not get to die.

395
00:32:45.465 --> 00:32:48.177
Your punishment is you will live
with what you have done.

396
00:32:52.097 --> 00:32:55.893
Death must be earned too. Witchfinder.
every bit as much as life.

397
00:32:55.976 --> 00:32:58.812
[breathes heavily]

398
00:33:19.750 --> 00:33:21.335
That's his favorite spot.

399
00:33:23.045 --> 00:33:26.715
And… his favorite chair.

400
00:33:28.008 --> 00:33:29.760
-Kerrigan. Come on.
-[groans]

401
00:33:29.843 --> 00:33:31.178
Wake the fuck up. Come on.

402
00:33:33.013 --> 00:33:36.808
[sniffs] Princess. [sighs]

403
00:33:36.892 --> 00:33:38.936
I can still smell the blossoms on you.

404
00:33:39.895 --> 00:33:43.565
You two should be home.
rolling around in sticky sheets.

405
00:33:43.649 --> 00:33:44.816
I need your help.

406
00:33:44.900 --> 00:33:49.404
-Brother. not up to the task?
-We need you to cross the border.

407
00:33:51.990 --> 00:33:53.408
What's the cargo?

408
00:33:53.992 --> 00:33:55.494
Her daughter. Haniwa.

409
00:33:56.995 --> 00:33:58.956
She's being held by the Trivantian army.

410
00:34:00.123 --> 00:34:01.708
-Oh.
-Yeah.

411
00:34:02.417 --> 00:34:03.627
Yeah. fuck off.

412
00:34:04.294 --> 00:34:05.587
Please.

413
00:34:05.671 --> 00:34:09.341
[Kerrigan]
Princess. generally in my trade.

414
00:34:09.424 --> 00:34:12.427
the object is to avoid the military.
not go searching for them.

415
00:34:12.511 --> 00:34:13.762
Kerrigan.

416
00:34:13.846 --> 00:34:16.306
[breathes heavily]

417
00:34:20.893 --> 00:34:24.898
If she really is in a military brig.
I won't be able to get her out.

418
00:34:24.982 --> 00:34:29.194
Come on. Prison guards can be bought.
same as anybody else.

419
00:34:29.277 --> 00:34:30.571
[Kerrigan] Maybe.

420
00:34:30.654 --> 00:34:33.197
But it would take a lot of copper.

421
00:34:33.282 --> 00:34:34.574
For you or for them?

422
00:34:35.951 --> 00:34:38.661
-I am offended. Princess.
-No. he's not.

423
00:34:40.205 --> 00:34:44.168
No. I suppose I'm not.
Still. it would take some doing.

424
00:34:44.668 --> 00:34:48.088
When you find her. how will you
get her safely out of Trivantes?

425
00:34:49.089 --> 00:34:51.091
[Kerrigan] Ah.
getting out of the city's the easy part.

426
00:34:51.175 --> 00:34:55.888
I have been smuggling Ganite thornflower
from Trivantes to Pennsa for years.

427
00:34:58.599 --> 00:35:04.813
I know every hole and tunnel
into and out of that place.

428
00:35:04.897 --> 00:35:07.399
-[inhales. groans]
-So you'll do it?

429
00:35:10.652 --> 00:35:16.366
[inhales]
Uh. consider it. um. a wedding gift.

430
00:35:17.993 --> 00:35:19.286
[yawns]

431
00:35:19.369 --> 00:35:21.997
I'll leave when the God Flame warms.

432
00:35:22.080 --> 00:35:23.749
-[Kerrigan yawns]
-You'll leave now.

433
00:35:24.499 --> 00:35:27.002
[kisses] Come on. Up you get.

434
00:36:04.081 --> 00:36:06.375
[Paris] No. Now is not the time.

435
00:36:09.002 --> 00:36:11.505
Paris? How could you bring him here?

436
00:36:11.588 --> 00:36:14.049
How could you even
share the air that he breathes?

437
00:36:14.132 --> 00:36:16.802
We need him. He has a new purpose.

438
00:36:16.885 --> 00:36:20.097
No. He dies by my hand tonight.

439
00:36:21.473 --> 00:36:23.559
[breathes shakily] He killed my mother.

440
00:36:23.642 --> 00:36:26.812
Yes. Time will come he pays for that.

441
00:36:27.688 --> 00:36:29.314
I can't believe this is you.

442
00:36:31.066 --> 00:36:32.150
You're a traitor.

443
00:36:32.693 --> 00:36:35.279
He is our only hope of getting to Maghra.

444
00:36:35.362 --> 00:36:37.781
The Witchfinders massacred the Valier.

445
00:36:39.408 --> 00:36:41.076
They will have
something to say about this.

446
00:36:41.159 --> 00:36:45.038
Please. You cannot tell them. You cannot.

447
00:36:47.207 --> 00:36:50.335
-I trusted you. I trusted you.
-Bow Lion. Bow Lion.

448
00:36:51.920 --> 00:36:52.921
You know me.

449
00:36:54.423 --> 00:36:56.675
You know my heart.

450
00:36:59.386 --> 00:37:00.846
-Girl.
-[cries]

451
00:37:03.473 --> 00:37:06.143
[Bow Lion sniffles]
Be gone before God Flame rises.

452
00:37:08.896 --> 00:37:11.190
I won't keep your secret
any longer than that.

453
00:37:38.175 --> 00:37:39.176
Kofun?

454
00:37:40.594 --> 00:37:42.387
[snapping]

455
00:37:45.098 --> 00:37:48.101
[sighs] Thank God Flame.

456
00:37:48.185 --> 00:37:49.520
[sighs]

457
00:37:50.062 --> 00:37:52.481
-I told you to stay in my room.
-I know.

458
00:37:53.440 --> 00:37:57.986
-I'm here.
-[Maghra breathes deeply]

459
00:37:58.570 --> 00:37:59.738
I'm sorry.

460
00:38:01.823 --> 00:38:06.161
I know this must all feel very strange
and upsetting to you.

461
00:38:06.245 --> 00:38:08.789
and I promise you
I will explain everything.

462
00:38:09.373 --> 00:38:12.167
but you cannot disobey me like that again.

463
00:38:12.251 --> 00:38:13.627
It is not safe here.

464
00:38:14.753 --> 00:38:16.713
-My sister is someone who--
-Sibeth.

465
00:38:18.674 --> 00:38:20.384
Don't worry. We've met.

466
00:38:22.010 --> 00:38:24.096
She came to see me after your wedding.

467
00:38:27.975 --> 00:38:29.017
Kofun.

468
00:38:31.895 --> 00:38:34.106
-You cannot trust her.
-[Kofun] Why not?

469
00:38:35.274 --> 00:38:37.693
She's not the one
who lied to me my entire life.

470
00:38:38.694 --> 00:38:39.695
[sighs]

471
00:38:40.779 --> 00:38:42.281
It is not that simple.

472
00:38:42.364 --> 00:38:43.699
[snaps]

473
00:38:43.782 --> 00:38:45.534
You betrayed your husband tonight.

474
00:38:46.827 --> 00:38:49.788
You betrayed all of us
and not for the first time.

475
00:38:51.206 --> 00:38:55.043
You could've identified yourself
to the Witchfinders when we were babies.

476
00:38:55.586 --> 00:38:57.796
You could've saved the Alkenny.

477
00:38:57.880 --> 00:38:59.590
We wouldn't have had to
spend our entire lives running.

478
00:38:59.673 --> 00:39:03.802
My sister would never have accepted
any sighted children that weren't her own.

479
00:39:05.429 --> 00:39:07.723
She would've killed all of us.

480
00:39:07.806 --> 00:39:10.309
I was trying to protect you
the best way I knew how.

481
00:39:10.392 --> 00:39:12.561
-By lying to us.
-Of course by lying to you.

482
00:39:12.644 --> 00:39:14.354
The truth would've gotten you
burned at the stake.

483
00:39:14.438 --> 00:39:15.439
No.

484
00:39:16.440 --> 00:39:21.778
You resented us.
You resented our sight. You always have.

485
00:39:22.779 --> 00:39:25.824
That's why you were so angry
when you realized we'd learned to read.

486
00:39:27.159 --> 00:39:28.160
Wasn't it?

487
00:39:29.828 --> 00:39:33.957
You wouldn't speak to us.
We'd become unrecognizable you said.

488
00:39:34.708 --> 00:39:37.169
Do you recognize yourself. Mama?

489
00:39:39.463 --> 00:39:40.631
Because I don't.

490
00:39:42.049 --> 00:39:46.512
You and Haniwa belong to a world
that I couldn't begin to understand.

491
00:39:48.222 --> 00:39:51.600
I was terrified that one day
it would take you away from me.

492
00:39:55.938 --> 00:39:57.231
Looks like it did.

493
00:40:03.028 --> 00:40:04.780
What are you doing about Haniwa and Dad?

494
00:40:07.950 --> 00:40:10.327
Lord Harlan has already
sent someone to find them.

495
00:40:12.412 --> 00:40:13.413
[scoffs]

496
00:40:15.165 --> 00:40:17.042
[laughs]

497
00:40:17.125 --> 00:40:20.462
Right. I'm sure your new husband
is very determined to find your old one.

498
00:40:44.236 --> 00:40:48.866
[Tamacti Jun sniffs. exhales]

499
00:40:54.204 --> 00:40:58.542
You asked me
if I remember how many I had killed.

500
00:41:02.296 --> 00:41:05.716
That's like me asking you
how many breaths you took today.

501
00:41:21.440 --> 00:41:25.402
When the queen left me bleeding to death…

502
00:41:28.071 --> 00:41:29.865
I fell into a state.

503
00:41:31.867 --> 00:41:35.954
Not dead… but no longer among the living.

504
00:41:40.250 --> 00:41:41.710
And it was there…

505
00:41:43.587 --> 00:41:44.796
suddenly…

506
00:41:47.591 --> 00:41:48.926
I had vision.

507
00:41:52.262 --> 00:41:54.473
[sniffs] Do you know what I saw?

508
00:42:01.188 --> 00:42:02.606
I saw faces.

509
00:42:05.108 --> 00:42:08.403
I saw the faces…

510
00:42:09.029 --> 00:42:14.743
of every man. woman and child
that I had murdered and tortured.

511
00:42:18.747 --> 00:42:20.290
I heard their screams.

512
00:42:23.001 --> 00:42:24.753
I could feel their pain.

513
00:42:30.300 --> 00:42:33.011
But in all of those faces…

514
00:42:35.639 --> 00:42:41.311
I could not find that of my wife
nor of my children.

515
00:42:46.233 --> 00:42:52.447
I was not there when Queen Kane
drowned them in their beds.

516
00:42:59.621 --> 00:43:00.873
Instead…

517
00:43:03.792 --> 00:43:08.380
I was butchering all those faces.

518
00:43:11.175 --> 00:43:16.054
For years and years.
you have fought for darkness.

519
00:43:19.349 --> 00:43:22.186
Now you must fight for light.

520
00:43:26.773 --> 00:43:29.193
You should not have stopped the girl.

521
00:43:35.199 --> 00:43:36.200
[grunts]

522
00:43:36.783 --> 00:43:40.871
All right. No more stopping.
We walk until we reach Pennsa.

523
00:43:41.830 --> 00:43:42.831
Do not fear.

524
00:43:44.666 --> 00:43:48.462
You will have
plenty of opportunities to die.

525
00:43:48.545 --> 00:43:49.588
[sniffs]

526
00:43:50.255 --> 00:43:51.465
We all will.

527
00:43:53.967 --> 00:43:58.388
[Haniwa] I always thought that
the fact that I could see and you couldn't

528
00:43:59.181 --> 00:44:01.016
was something that separated us.

529
00:44:02.684 --> 00:44:04.895
Thought there was
so much space between us.

530
00:44:05.521 --> 00:44:09.608
But every time
I feel like I'm beyond help.

531
00:44:10.817 --> 00:44:16.031
in the House of Enlightenment.
in Trivantes. somehow you always find me.

532
00:44:19.493 --> 00:44:24.206
You're my baby girl.
Kofun is my boy. Maghra my wife.

533
00:44:25.082 --> 00:44:29.628
As long as I'm alive.
nothing will separate us. Yes.

534
00:44:33.757 --> 00:44:35.342
I know I don't make it easy.

535
00:44:38.262 --> 00:44:39.471
No. you don't.

536
00:44:41.181 --> 00:44:43.058
From this place. it's two days to Pennsa.

537
00:44:45.727 --> 00:44:48.230
What do you think it will be like. Pennsa?

538
00:44:50.065 --> 00:44:51.066
Crowded.

539
00:44:52.401 --> 00:44:55.028
[chuckles]
What do you think she'll be like?

540
00:44:56.405 --> 00:44:58.824
-Uh. she'll be like Maghra.
-Right.

541
00:45:00.742 --> 00:45:02.661
Do we even know who that is?

